======================================================================
SEESAW INTERACTION WITH GOOD VERTEX
======================================================================

By adjacent-odd seesaw: beta_1 * beta_3 = 0.
So if beta_3(T) = 1, then beta_1(T) = 0.
Question: does beta_1(T\v) = 0 also hold for some/all v?
If so, the LES at level 1 simplifies.

  When beta_3(T)=1 at n=6, (beta_1(T\v), beta_3(T\v)) distribution:
    (0, 0): 1920
